# Coach Tracker — environment variables (EXAMPLE / placeholder)
#
# This app is a 100% static, frontend-only tool. It needs NO secrets and NO API
# keys to run — all data lives in the browser's localStorage.
#
# This file exists only as a placeholder so that IF you later add an optional
# integration (e.g. a cloud sync backend), you have a documented pattern:
#   1. Copy this file to `.env`  ->  cp .env.example .env
#   2. Fill in real values in `.env` (which is git-ignored — never committed)
#   3. In Vercel, add the same keys under Project Settings -> Environment Variables
#
# Example placeholder (NOT used by the current app):
# COACH_TRACKER_SYNC_API_URL=https://example.com/api
# COACH_TRACKER_SYNC_API_KEY=your-key-here
